# Module layout & URL routing

## File locations for module `X`

| Concern | Legacy (`modules/X/`) | Modern (`src/Modules/X/`) |
|---|---|---|
| Controller (View) | `modules/X/views/<View>.php` | `src/Modules/X/Views/<View>.php` |
| Action | `modules/X/actions/<Action>.php` | `src/Modules/X/Actions/<Action>.php` |
| Model | `modules/X/models/<Model>.php` | `src/Modules/X/Models/<Model>.php` |
| Smarty templates | `layouts/basic/modules/X/*.tpl` | same |
| JS/CSS | `public/layouts/basic/modules/X/resources/*.js` | same |
| Language strings | `languages/<lang>/X.php` | same |

## URL → file mapping

- `index.php?module=X&view=V`     → `views/V.php` (or `Views/V.php`)
- `index.php?module=X&action=A`   → `actions/A.php` (typically AJAX/POST)
- `index.php?parent=Settings&module=X&view=V` → `src/Modules/Settings/X/Views/V.php`

## Adding a new view/action

1. Class name = file basename (e.g. `Edit.php` defines `<Module>_Edit_View` or `App\Modules\<Module>\Views\Edit`).
2. Wire the URL with `view=` or `action=` — no router config needed.
3. For Settings views, extend `App\Modules\Settings\Base\Views\Index` to inherit the menu.
